# React Component Patterns

- Functional components with TypeScript, no class components
- Props interfaces defined inline or co-located in the same file
- State management via `useState` — no external state library
- Animations via `motion/react` (Motion library, successor to Framer Motion)
- Icons from `lucide-react`
- Styling with Tailwind CSS 4 utility classes inline

## Design System tokens (use Tailwind tokens, not raw hex)

- Primary yellow: `bg-partrunner-yellow` (`#FFD840`)
- Black: `text-partrunner-black` (`#14142B`)
- Page bg: `bg-partrunner-bg-main` (`#F5F7FB`)
- Cards: `bg-partrunner-bg-card` (white)
- Borders: `border-partrunner-gray-light` (`#D9DBE9`)
- Body text: `text-partrunner-gray-dark` (`#4E4B66`)
- Use `.btn-primary`, `.card`, `.input-base` CSS classes from index.css

## UI theme

- Light theme (NOT dark)
- Header: yellow background with black logo/text
- Cards: white with subtle shadow
- Font: Inter only

## Step state machine

The app uses a `Step` type: `"input" | "transforming" | "transformed" | "generating" | "complete"`.
All UI conditional rendering is based on this state.

## Error handling

```tsx
catch (err: unknown) {
  const msg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : "Error desconocido";
  setError(msg);
}
```
